  "texts": [
    "The apparent hexagonal pattern in (g) is a finite-size artifact that diminishes with increasing system size.?",
    "PM Q L R O AFM NM ℤ + 6 ⊕ ℤ 2 FM ℤ + 6 NM ℤ 2 AFM NM ℤ - 6 ⊕ ℤ 2 Q L R O N M ⊕ ℤ 2?",
    "AFM NM ℤ + 6 ⊕ ℤ 2 NM ℤ 2 QLRO NM ⊕ ℤ 2 PM AFM NM ℤ -two prominent peaks separated by π reflect standard AFM order.",
    "In contrast, the Z - q phase shows two pairs of peaks of nearly equal frequencies.",
    "Within each pair the peaks are separated by 2π/q, and the pairs themselves are spaced by π relative to their midpoint -highlighting AFM order built from emergent (2k + 1)π/q spin states.Order parameters and observables.-To characterize the various phases and locate transition boundaries, we examine several observables and order parameters (see Fig. 1(e))."
